                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d627">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Powell reports that Admiral Killick prevents the steamship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Paloma</hi> from entering Cape Haitian; that he has cabled to Commander
                    McCrea, at Gonaives, that the Haitian Government is not recognized, nor the
                    blockade of the Cape, and to give protection to any American, Cuban, or foreign
                    vessel desiring to enter Cape, informing Admiral Killick of his intention.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
